&lt;h2&gt;The role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a hands-on engineering manager to drive the strategy, execution, and growth of Hex’s state-of-the-art AI context platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ambition is simple but powerful: Hex should get better every time you use it. With tens of thousands of people relying on Hex daily to do deep analytical work, we are uniquely positioned to learn from usage and continuously improve the intelligence of our system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The context platform is at the heart of this vision. It is the surface area where users can understand how AI agents interact with their data, identify where quality falls short, and actively improve the context that drives better outcomes. We are building an entirely new development lifecycle for context, one that blends human insight with automated learning and iteration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The broader AI landscape is evolving quickly, and our team is tackling foundational questions such as how to detect and debug failures in agent reasoning, how to structure and manage business context effectively, how to balance human-in-the-loop systems with autonomous improvement, and how to integrate our context layer with the growing ecosystem of AI-powered tools and workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a team working on Hex’s context platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive technical strategy, review designs, and directly contribute with hands-on work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as people manager for the engineers on the team, setting a high bar and empowering them to do their best work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit exceptional engineering talent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience as a full-stack software engineer and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years experience leading engineering teams working on complex, data-intensive, or AI-driven products and SaaS platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional ability to identify and design the right technical abstractions to accelerate an ambitious and evolving product vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep curiosity for, and strong intuition about, state-of-the-art AI agent behavior and context systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record as a people manager, with experience building and operating product engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
