&lt;h2&gt;The role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced full-stack &lt;strong&gt;Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Growth &amp;amp; Monetization group. This group spans several work streams — including product-led growth (PLG), user activation, pricing and billing, and new product bets —solving complex challenges that help thousands of customers, from startups to Fortune 500 companies, get the most out of Hex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for an engineer who thinks like a business owner and has strong product sense. You won&#39;t just write code—you&#39;ll obsess over conversion rates, user experience, business tradeoffs, and what makes a user go from &quot;this is interesting&quot; to &quot;I can&#39;t live without this.&quot; Together with your Product, Design, Data, and Marketing partners, you’ll be responsible for driving key business outcomes for Hex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our PLG motion is core to how Hex grows. Every day, thousands of data scientists and analysts discover Hex, sign up, and explore. You’ll be a key member of the team turning that interest into lasting engagement and revenue—through experimentation, product improvements, and an unrelenting focus on moving the dial for the business. If you&#39;ve ever wished you could combine the rigor of engineering with the impact of running a business, this is the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time role that can be held from one of our New York, NY or San Francisco, CA hubs, or remotely in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do at Hex&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build growth-focused product features&lt;/strong&gt;: Create full-stack experiences (in React, Typescript, Python, and more) like onboarding flows, core product features, activation nudges, and billing experiences that feel delightful and drive results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balance experimentation with product sense&lt;/strong&gt;: Design, run, and iterate on A/B tests across the funnel when it’s appropriate; lean on product sense and customer input when it’s not.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive growth metrics&lt;/strong&gt;: With your team, take responsibility for key business outcomes like trial-to-paid conversion, user activation rates, expansion revenue, or product-led pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate across the business&lt;/strong&gt;: Work closely with Product, Design, Data, and Marketing to identify opportunities and align on growth priorities. You&#39;ll have a seat at the table when we discuss strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instrument and analyze everything&lt;/strong&gt;: Build robust tracking, define success metrics, and use data to inform every decision. At Hex, you&#39;ll have the best data tools at your fingertips (we literally build them), as well as a strong foundation of tracking and experiment infrastructure (Eppo, LanchDarkly, Ampli).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 4+ years of experience as a full-stack software engineer—comfortable building across frontend (React/TypeScript) and backend systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You operate with a “business owner&quot; mindset: driving business outcomes and delivering value to customers matter more to you than writing perfect code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re pragmatic with good data intuition. You’re just as comfortable making fast decisions on imperfect data as you are setting up tracking and running stat-sig experiments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You default to action—shipping fast, learning quickly, and iterating relentlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re familiar with B2B SaaS, experimentation, billing, and/or collaboration products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;It’s a bonus if you have:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at a product-led growth (PLG) company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in analytics, data tools, or developer-foc

&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Staff or Principal-level software engineer to join our Compute team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hex&#39;s Compute team owns one of the hardest performance problems in the product: our users do everything from analyzing 100-line CSV files to querying petabyte-scale Snowflake tables, and in all cases they expect it to feel fast. We power a technical product that our customers trust to accurately retrieve data from their own systems to then efficiently execute polyglot backed analytics workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a backend-heavy role with a focus on computation, performance, data systems design, and systems architecture. You&#39;ll drive architectural decisions that compound over years, write the technical designs that shape how the team builds, and directly influence the long-term trajectory of Hex&#39;s compute platform — all while staying deeply hands-on in the codebase.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolve Hex&#39;s execution architecture — the graph-based system that compiles, plans, and runs user notebooks — including proposing and building entirely new compute components that support faster, smarter execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive parallel execution strategies and caching approaches that reduce latency and minimize unnecessary round trips to external data warehouses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instrument complex systems to surface and diagnose performance problems to give the team and our customers a much clearer picture of where time is being spent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across engineering and product to support new platform capabilities, such as building an internal query language that compiles to the appropriate dialect for any connected warehouse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author and review technical proposals, and mentor engineers to implement ambitious designs effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose and roadmap long-term designs with clear milestones across quarters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of backend engineering experience, with a strong focus on computation, performance, database/storage optimization, and systems architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with parallel execution strategies, caching strategies, and the trade-offs involved in remote data warehouse computation. Strong systems thinker with solid intuitions around storage, database performance, algorithms, and data structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of solving difficult, large-scale systems design problems involving significant data and operational complexity — writing code and reviewing code of your teammates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to move from abstract, vague problems to well-articulated, well-reasoned technical solutions — and to roadmap ambitious designs with clear milestones across quarters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong communicator; comfortable leading technical work and collaborating across a remote-first team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Python and/or TypeScript required; experience with both is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Kubernetes, Docker and cloud infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some frontend experience — this is a backend-focused role, but a willingness to occasionally wire a feature all the way through is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is fully remote anywhere within the US Eastern timezone, with the option to work from our NYC office.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
